  <description>Herbs, annual, 0.4-6 dm. Stems simple or freely branched, decumbent, ascending, or
        erect. Leaf blades narrowly to broadly elliptic, lanceolate, oblong, or ovate, (1-)2-9 ×
        0.4-3 cm, base narrowly cuneate, apex acuminate to long-attenuate or obtuse to rounded;
        proximal pair of lateral veins arising above junction of blade and petiole. Flowers:
        involucral bracts 1.8-5 mm, usually less than 2 times length of achene; tepals 1.5-2 mm,
        shorter than bracts. Achenes light brown, symmetric, 0.9-1.2 × 0.6-0.9 mm, apex obtuse,
        mucro apical; stipe straight, short-cylindric, centered, basally dilated. 2n=14,
        16.</description>
  <phenology>Flowering spring-late fall</phenology>
  <habitat>Dry ledges, talus slopes, waste and shaded places, primarily in neutral to basic
        soils, and reported from margins of hot springs in northernmost locations</habitat>
